name "sec: theory"

\end_inset

 We derived the theoretical value of the splitting 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta \nu $
\end_inset

 caused by the Zeeman effect, as a linear function of the magnetic field 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 (equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: splitting"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

). The full derivation is included in the Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: theory derivation"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

. 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \Delta \nu = \frac{g_{eff} \mu_B}{hc} B \label{eq: splitting}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

The splitting is linearly dependent on the effective LandÃ© g-factor 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{eff}$
\end_inset

 given by equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: g eff"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    g_{eff} = g_{L_2} m_{J_2} - g_{L_1} m_{J_1} \label{eq: g eff}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

for a transition 
\begin_inset Formula $2 \rightarrow 1$
\end_inset

. The splitting is a function of the 
\begin_inset Formula $m_J$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 quantum numbers: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    g_L = 1 + \frac{j(j+1)-l(l+1) +s(s+1)}{j(j+1)} \label{eq: gl}
\end{equation}
\end_inset


