\begin_layout Subsection
Cadmium green transition - anomalous Zeeman effect
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec: Cd green"

\end_inset

 The 
\begin_inset Formula $5^3 S_1\rightarrow 5^3 P_2$
\end_inset

 transition, for the cadmium green line, exhibits the anomalous Zeeman effect: the spin of the electrons couple together and the interaction involves both the orbit and angular momentum and the spin angular momentum. The anomalous Zeeman effect splits the spectral line in more than three components that are not necessarily equally spaced apart. The effective g-factor values, derived using Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: quantum_numbers"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: g eff"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 are shown in Table 
